examples.en: It mists / it is misting.
The windows have misted up.
The hills were clothed in mist.
Her eyes misted over with tears.
The mist thickened.
The old castle was involved in mist.
A thick mist hung over the town.
The plant should be misted regularly.
examples.ru: Это растение следует регулярно сбрызгивать водой.

examples.en: Mist shrouded the castle.
The sun soon dispersed the mist.
When morning came, the mist had vanished away.
A dim mist shelled the god.
A mist filmed over the stars.
We could hardly see for the mist.
examples.ru: Из-за тумана нам почти ничего не было видно.

examples.en: The light couldn't penetrate through the mist.
Mist rolled in from the sea.
A cotton wool mist descended.
As the sun got hotter, it sucked up the mist from the sea.
examples.ru: По мере того, как солнце пригревало все сильнее и сильнее, дымка, висящая над морем, исчезала.

examples.en: It was misting when we arrived.
examples.ru: Когда мы приехали, был небольшой туман.

examples.en: The windshield misted over.
The view was obscured by mist.
The cliff was shrouded in mist.
Thick mist clouded the mountaintops.
The mountains were wreathed in mist.
The plant has to be misted every day.
examples.ru: Это растение нужно каждый день сбрызгивать водой.

examples.en: The hills were veiled in a fine mist.
We could barely make out some figures moving in the mist.
examples.ru: Мы едва могли разобрать какие-то фигуры, движущиеся в тумане.

examples.en: The grassy hills were sheathed in mist.
examples.ru: Заросшие травой холмы были скрыты туманом.

examples.en: The river was sliding darkly under the mist.
examples.ru: Река плавно несла свои воды в темноте, под покровом тумана.

examples.en: Mist eddied round the house.
